n local residue\\\", with vendors uneven across those three layers.\\n\\n## Next\\n\\n- Produce batch 008 as a narrow propagation-lag / stale-state-window pass.\\n- Center batch 008 on:\\n  - eventual consistency after delete/remove,\\n  - policy-apply latency,\\n  - background-job cadence,\\n  - delayed catalog refresh visibility,\\n  - grace periods before cleanup really lands,\\n  - and any first-party alerting for stale state.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/research/theme-signal-radar-runner/logs/iteration_008.log:104:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_52\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '1,260p' ../memory/CONTEXT.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# Theme Signal Radar Context\\n\\n## Fact\\n\\n- Shared workspace:\\n  - `workspace/theme-exploration-shared` points to `/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/research/theme-exploration-shared`.\\n  - Write output only to `signals/`.\\n- Signal standard:\\n  - Separate facts, inferences, and recommendations.\\n  - Preserve source URLs for every factual claim.\\n  - Prefer primary or near-primary sources.\\n  - Mark confidence as high, medium, or low.\\n  - Do not invent missing facts; weak sourcing requires an evidence-gap note.\\n- 2026-05-04: created `theme-exploration-shared/signals/2026-05-04-signal-radar-batch-001.md` with 31 source-backed signals across AI agents, coding agents, AI devtools, AI infra/pricing, creative AI, local-first tools, open-source productization, and content automation.\\n- 2026-05-04: created `theme-exploration-shared/signals/2026-05-05-signal-radar-batch-002.md` with 12 protocol/distribution signals on MCP, A2A, ACP, managed endpoints, registry surfaces, and IDE support.\\n- 2026-05-04: created queued file `theme-exploration-shared/signals/2026-05-06-signal-radar-batch-003.md` with 10 control-plane signals across approvals, auth, quotas, sandboxing, registry trust, and tool-surface minimization.\\n