ms.\\n\\n## Next\\n\\n- Produce batch 009 as a narrow reversibility / partial-restore pass.\\n- Center batch 009 on:\\n  - restore windows and undelete deadlines,\\n  - availability lag before restore becomes possible,\\n  - what metadata or permissions fail to come back after restore,\\n  - pending-disable side effects that continue during grace periods,\\n  - and state-loss edges where rollback is only partial.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/research/theme-signal-radar-runner/logs/iteration_021.log:22:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_10\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' /Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/research/theme-signal-radar-runner/memory/CONTEXT.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# Theme Signal Radar Context\\n\\n## Fact\\n\\n- Shared workspace:\\n  - `workspace/theme-exploration-shared` points to `/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/research/theme-exploration-shared`.\\n  - Write output only to `signals/`.\\n- Signal standard:\\n  - Separate facts, inferences, and recommendations.\\n  - Preserve source URLs for every factual claim.\\n  - Prefer primary or near-primary sources.\\n  - Mark confidence as high, medium, or low.\\n  - Do not invent missing facts; weak sourcing requires an evidence-gap note.\\n- 2026-05-04: created `theme-exploration-shared/signals/2026-05-04-signal-radar-batch-001.md` with 31 source-backed signals across AI agents, coding agents, AI devtools, AI infra/pricing, creative AI, local-first tools, open-source productization, and content automation.\\n- 2026-05-04: created `theme-exploration-shared/signals/2026-05-05-signal-radar-batch-002.md` with 12 protocol/distribution signals on MCP, A2A, ACP, managed endpoints, registry surfaces, and IDE support.\\n- 2026-05-04: created queued file `theme-exploration-shared/signals/2026-05-06-signal-radar-batch-003.md` with 10 control-plane signals across approvals, auth, quotas, sandboxing, registr